Program: Free Thinking
Title: The pros and cons of Swearing
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09c0r4m
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 2 Nov 2017
Comedian Janey Godley, historian John Gallagher, poet and journalist Bridget Minamore and author and science writer Dr Emma Byrne discuss with Matthew Sweet swearing on stage, in pain and protest and when new terms entered our language. Swearing Is Good For You by Emma Byrne is out now. Please note this programme may contain strong language. Producer: Debbie Kilbride. Show less